<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What happens to velocity in MV = PY when new financial technology makes transactions more efficient?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Velocity decreases because less money is needed</option>
            <option letter="b">Velocity increases because each dollar is used more frequently</option>
            <option letter="c">Velocity stays constant regardless of technology</option>
            <option letter="d">Velocity becomes more volatile</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>When financial technology improves transaction efficiency, each dollar can be used more frequently for transactions. This increases velocity (V) because the same amount of money can support more transactions, meaning each dollar circulates through the economy more quickly.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
